Context: The Assessment Centre at George Brown College offers admission/placement assessments both online and in-person. Test takers are required to book appointments through STU-VIEW, paying attention to sessions indicated with an "(S)" at 200 King Street Room 275. The college strictly adheres to the Academic Integrity policy, prohibiting dishonest academic conduct during testing. Free online MSAP evening courses are available for application, and applicants can sign up to receive updates about application deadlines, college news, upcoming events, tours, and more via email. Contact information includes the phone number 416-415-2000 and TTY 1-877-515-5559, as well as the email address ask.george@georgebrown.ca. The website's content is subject to change without notice.
